The paper deals with semantic segmentation in remote sensing images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel deep convolutional neural network architecture for sea-land segmentation, which falls under the category of graphics (cs.GR). The paper also discusses the performance of the network and compares it with other architectures, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with remote sensing imagery, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
